    <etym xml:lang="ru">Общеиранское слово; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
            ><lang/><w>āvēz-</w></mentioned>: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><lang/><w>āvēxt-</w><gloss><q>висеть</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>вешать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><w>āvēng, āvingān</w><gloss><q>висящий</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="ku"><lang/><w>halavisin</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"
                ><lang/><w>avezun</w><gloss><q>вешать</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Sköld._Pam."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1936, стр.
                212</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1936, p. 212</biblScope></bibl>); сращение
        префикса %iā%i с основой %i*vik-%i, %i*vink-%i, которую с другой огласовкой находим,
        по-видимому, в <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>vañc-,
                vañg-</w><gloss><q>шататься</q></gloss></mentioned>, куда примыкает <mentioned
            xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>wanken</w></mentioned>. Более отдаленная по звуковому облику, но
        близкая по значению связь — со <mentioned xml:lang="cu"
                ><lang/><w>висѣти</w></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"
                /><biblScope>II 78</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>24, 63</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Common Iranian word; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
            ><lang/><w>āvēz-</w></mentioned>: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><lang/><w>āvēxt-</w><gloss><q>hang</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>hang up</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><w>āvēng, āvingān</w><gloss><q>hanging</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="ku"><lang/><w>halavisin</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"
                ><lang/><w>avezun</w><gloss><q>hang up</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Sköld._Pam."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1936, стр.
                212</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1936, p. 212</biblScope></bibl>); fusion of
        the prefix %iā%i with the stem %i*vik-%i, %i*vink-%i which, with a different vocalization,
        we find, apparently, in <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>vañc-,
                    vañg-</w><gloss><q>stagger</q></gloss></mentioned>, to which is adjacent
            <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>wanken</w></mentioned>. More distant phonetically,
        but close semantically is the connection with <mentioned xml:lang="cu"
                    ><lang/><w>висѣти</w><gloss><q>hang</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 78</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>24, 63</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
